text: Patissa latifuscalis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by George Hampson in 1896. It is found in Assam, India. The wingspan is about 26 mm. The forewings are white with a fuscous black costal area and a black basal patch, as well as a black medial band. There is a fuscous postmedial line on the hindwings.Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London 1895: 910 ==References== Category:Moths described in 1896 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Patissa latifuscalis
